# Stack config vs local-only environment

## Stack configuration (commit to git)

Reproducible platform definition shared by all environments:

- `docker-compose.yml`, `sample.env` (template only — never commit real `.env`)
- `keycloak/realm-export.json` (applied on **first** Keycloak import only)
- `postgres/init/`, `sonarqube/`, `bootstrap/`, `api/`, `console/`, `configs/`, tracked `__DOCS__/`
- One-shot compose services: `*-init`, `sonarqube-config-init`, `sonarqube-init`
- Optional **maintainer** scripts (not required for normal `docker compose up`): e.g. `bootstrap/reset-sonarqube.sh`, `bootstrap/reset.sh`

Greenfield path: copy `sample.env` → `.env`, then `make bootstrap` / `docker compose up -d`. Do not require machine-specific recovery scripts for first install.

When changing stack behavior, update **both** code and docs (`__DOCS__/`, `99_maintainers/02_services.md` where relevant). Existing Keycloak realms need manual or scripted client patches documented in `__DOCS__/02_admin/09_sonarqube_sso.md` — `realm-export.json` does not re-apply.

## Local-only (never commit)

Per-developer or runtime state — **exclude from stack PRs**:

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.env` | Secrets, domains (`SONARQUBE_DOMAIN`, passwords, tokens) |
| `.vols/` | Postgres, GitLab, Sonar data, generated `sonar.properties`, bootstrap markers |
| `_local/` | Gitignored scratch tools (legacy Vite UI may remain under `_local/management-ui/`) |
| Ad-hoc Keycloak Admin UI clicks | Live realm DB; document procedure, do not assume export re-import |

Troubleshooting (reset Sonar, patch SAML client, rotate creds) belongs in **local ops** or optional bootstrap scripts, not in the default install path unless promoted intentionally to stack docs.

## Operator console

Shipped as `console/` (Next.js at `https://console.devops.<DOMAIN>`, oauth2-proxy `admins` group). GraphQL calls go through server-side BFF routes with `API_KEY` — never expose the key in the browser.

After API schema changes under `api/src/projects/graphql/`, update `console/src/lib/graphql.ts`, `console/src/lib/types.ts`, and affected components in the same session. See `.cursor/rules/console.mdc`.

## Commits

- One PR/commit theme per stack concern (API, Sonar ops, infra), not mixed with local recovery notes.
- Do not stage `.env`, `.vols/`, or `_local/`.
